quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,141,"those who lie in wait for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, so if there is a conquest for you from Allah, they say, “Were we not with you?” While if the deniers have any measure<i class=""s"">(of success) </i>, they say, “Did we not have privilege over you and defend you from the believers?” Then Allah will judge between you on the Day of Resurrection. And Allah will never grant any way for the deniers against the believers."
  4,142,"Indeed, the hypocrites try to deceive Allah, while He deceives them. And when they rise for prayer they rise lazily, for show in front of mankind. And they do not remember Allah except a little,"
  4,143,"wavering in between, neither with these nor with these. For whomever Allah leads astray—then you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>will not find any way for him."
  4,144,"O you who have attained faith, do not take the deniers as allies apart from the believers. Do you want to give Allah evident proof against you?"
  4,145,"Indeed, the hypocrites are in the lowest level of the Fire, and you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>will not find any supporter for them—"
  4,146,"except those who repented and reformed and held fast to Allah and dedicated their religion faithfully to Allah, for those are with the believers, and Allah will bring the believers a great reward."
  4,147,"What would Allah do with your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>punishment if you have given thanks and have attained faith, when Allah has always been Thankful, All-Knowing?"
